.W. Gaunt & Sons | series=W.I.L.I.P. series | year=1987 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7_fpD9s0V2AC&q=Miss+World+1981|page=92 | quote=They enthusiastically choose a Miss Jamaica Universe each May and a Miss Jamaica World each September And there are ... have been second runners-up in the Miss World finals \u2014 Debbie Campbell in 1979 and Sandra Cunningham in 1981.}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=center | '''60''' || '''{{flag|Mexico}}''' || Doris Pontvianne Espinoza || 18\n|-\n| align=center | '''61''' || '''{{flag|Peru}}''' || Olga Roxana Zumar\u00e1n Burga || 22\n|-\n| align=center | '''62''' || '''{{flag|Puerto Rico|1952}}''' || Andrenira Ruiz S\u00e1enz || 19\n|-\n| align=center | '''63''' || '''{{flag|Suriname}}''' || Joan Boldewijn || 18\n|-\n| align=center | '''64''' || '''{{flag|Trinidad & Tobago}}''' || Rachel Ann Thomas || 21\n|-\n| align=center | '''65''' || '''{{flag|United States}}''' || Lisa Lynn Moss || 23\n|-\n| align=center | '''66''' || '''{{flag|Uruguay}}''' || Silvia Marianela Bas Carrese || 23\n|-\n| align=center | '''67''' || '''{{flag|Venezuela|1954}}''' || [[Pil\u00edn Le\u00f3n]] || 18 <ref name=\"Rome News-Tribune\"/><ref name=\"Weeks\"/>\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n===Returns===\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n*Last competed in [[Miss World 1966|1966]]:\n** '''{{flagu|Suriname}}'''\n*Last competed in [[Miss World 1979|1979]]:\n** '''{{flagu|Chile}}'''\n** '''{{flagu|El Salvador}}'''\n** '''{{flagu|Iceland}}'''\n** '''{{flagu|Tahiti}}'''\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Withdrawals===\n* '''{{flagu|Panama}}'''\n* '''{{flagu|Paraguay}}'''\n* '''{{flagu|Swaziland}}'''\n* '''{{flagu|Portugal}}''' \u2013 Paula Dos Santos who had a dual citizenship, won the Miss Portugal contest held in Johannesburg, South Africa. She flew to London, only to be told by Eric Morley that any girl from South Africa cannot participate, and that the contest has to be held in the country of the girl's origin.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs= \n<ref name=\"Weeks\">{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2245&dat=19860813&id=6uIzAAAAIBAJ&sjid=nTIHAAAAIBAJ&pg=6730,5611442&hl=en | title=Venezuelan beauties undergo rigorous training to win international pageants | newspaper=[[Lodi News-Sentinel]] | date=August 13, 1986 | accessdate=25 January 2016 | author=Weeks, Sally}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* [https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2194&dat=19810910&id=na4yAAAAIBAJ&sjid=y-4FAAAAIBAJ&pg=6495,5007549&hl=en ''Ottawa Citizen'']. September 10, 1981.\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081218082833/http://www.pageantopolis.com/international/world_1981.htm Pageantopolis \u2013 Miss World 1981]\n\n{{Miss World}}\n\n[[Category:Miss World]]\n[[Category:1981 in London]]\n[[Category:1981 beauty pageants]]\n[[Category:Beauty pageants in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Events at the Royal Albert Hall]]\n[[Category:November 1981 events in the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox beauty pageant\n| photo = [[File:MW 1981 - Thames TV.png|250px]]\n| caption = Miss World 1981 Titlecard\n| winner = '''[[Pil\u00edn Le\u00f3n]]''' <br> '''{{flag|Venezuela|1954}}'''\n| date = 12 November 1981\n| presenters = [[Peter Marshall (UK broadcaster)|Peter Marshall]], [[Judith Chalmers]]\n| venue = [[Royal Albert Hall]], London, UK<ref name=\"Ribane 2006\"/> \n| broadcaster = [[Thames Television]]\n| entrants = 67\n| placements = 15\n| returns = [[Chile]], [[El Salvador]], [[Iceland]], [[Suriname]], [[Tahiti]]\n| withdraws = [[Mauritius]], [[Panama]], [[Paraguay]], [[Swaziland]], [[American Virgin Islands]]\n| before = [[Miss World 1980|1980]]\n| next = [[Miss World 1982|1982]]\n}}\n\n'''Miss World 1981''', the 31st edition of the [[Miss World]] pageant, was held on 12 November 1981 at the [[Royal Albert Hall]] in London, UK.<ref name=\"Ribane 2006\"/><ref name=\"Rome News-Tribune\">{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=348&dat=19811113&id=tNsvAAAAIBAJ&sjid=mTQDAAAAIBAJ&pg=3639,2277690&hl=en | title=New Miss World | newspaper=[[Rome News-Tribune]] | date=November 13, 1981 | accessdate=25 January 2016}}</ref> The winner was [[Pil\u00edn Le\u00f3n]] from Venezuela,<ref name=\"Rome News-Tribune\"/><ref name=\"Weeks\"/> the first titleholder from her country since [[Miss World 1955|1955]]. She was crowned by Miss World 1980, [[Kimberley Santos]] of [[Guam]]. Another Venezuelan, [[Irene S\u00e1ez]], had been crowned [[Miss Universe 1981]] in July, making Venezuela one of the very few countries to hold both major international titles ([[Miss Universe]] and [[Miss World]]) in the same year. The titles of Continental Queens of Beauty were awarded for the very first time.\n\n==Results==\n[[File:Miss World 1981 Map.PNG|thumb|250px|Countries and territories which sent delegates and results for Miss World 1981<ref name=\"Ribane 2006\"/><ref name=\"Weeks\"/><ref name=\"W.W. Gaunt & Sons 1987\"/>]]\n\n===Placements===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n! Final results\n! Contestant\n|-\n| '''Miss World 1981'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Venezuela|1954}}''' \u2013 '''[[Pil\u00edn Le\u00f3n]]'''<ref name=\"Rome News-Tribune\"/><ref name=\"Weeks\"/> \n|-\n| '''1st runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Colombia}}''' \u2013 Nini Johanna Soto\n|-\n| '''2nd runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Jamaica}}''' \u2013 Sandra Cunningham\n|-\n| '''3rd runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Brazil|1968}}''' \u2013 Maristela Grazzia\n|-\n| '''4th runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|United Kingdom}}''' \u2013 Michelle Donnelly\n|-\n| '''5th runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Australia}}''' \u2013 [[Melissa Hannan]]\n|-\n| '''6th runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|United States}}''' \u2013 Lisa Lynn Moss\n|-\n| '''Semi-finalists'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Argentina}}''' \u2013 Ana Natali Schoeder Belmut\n* '''{{flag|Belgium}}''' \u2013 Dominique van Eeckhoudt\n* '''{{flag|Canada}}''' \u2013 Earla Stewart\n* '''{{flag|Ireland}}''' \u2013 Geraldine McGrory\n* '''{{flag|Japan|1947}}''' \u2013 Naomi Kishi\n* '''{{flag|Mexico}}''' \u2013 Doris Pontvianne\n* '''{{flag|Trinidad & Tobago}}''' \u2013 Rachel Thomas\n* '''{{flag|Zimbabwe}}''' \u2013 Juliet Nyathi\n|}\n\n===Continental Queens of Beauty===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n! Continental Group\n! Contestant\n|-\n| '''Africa'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Zimbabwe}}''' \u2013 Juliet Nyathi\n|-\n| '''Americas'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Venezuela|1954}}''' \u2013 [[Pil\u00edn Le\u00f3n]]\n|-\n| '''Asia'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Japan|1947}}''' \u2013 Naomi Kishi\n|-\n| '''Europe'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|United Kingdom}}''' \u2013 Michele Donnelly\n|-\n| '''Oceania'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Australia}}''' \u2013 [[Melissa Hannan]]\n|}\n\n==Contestants==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- \n! colspan=4 | EUROPE\n|- \n! Number || Nation || Contestant || Age\n|-\n| align=center | '''01''' || '''{{flag|Austria}}''' || Beatrix Kopf || 21\n|-\n| align=center | '''02''' || '''{{flag|Belgium}}''' || Dominique van Eeckhoudt ||  20\n|-\n| align=center | '''03''' || '''{{flag|Cyprus}}''' || Elena Andreou || 19\n|-\n| align=center | '''04''' || '''{{flag|Denmark}}''' || Tina Brandstrup || 21\n|-\n| align=center | '''05''' || '''{{flag|Finland}}''' || Pia Irmeli Ann-Marie Nieminen || 20\n|-\n| align=center | '''06''' || '''{{flag|France}}''' || Isabelle Sophie Ben\u00e1rd || 19\n|-\n| align=center | '''07''' || '''{{flag|Germany}}''' || Barbara Reimund || 18\n|-\n| align=center | '''08''' || '''{{flag|Gibraltar|ensign}}''' || Yvette Maria Bellido || 18\n|-\n| align=center | '''09''' || '''{{flag|Greece}}''' || Maria Argirocastritou || 22\n|-\n| align=center | '''10''' || '''{{flag|Holland}}''' || Saskia Lemmens || 23\n|-\n| align=center | '''11''' || '''{{flag|Iceland}}''' || \u00c1sd\u00eds Eva Hannesd\u00f3ttir || 23\n|-\n| align=center | '''12''' || '''{{flag|Ireland}}''' || Geraldine Mary McGrory || 22\n|-\n| align=center | '''13''' || '''{{flag|Isle of Man}}''' || Nicola Jane Grainger || 18\n|-\n| align=cent