 Le\u00f3n]] || 18 <ref name=\"Rome News-Tribune\"/><ref name=\"Weeks\"/>\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n===Returns===\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n*Last competed in [[Miss World 1966|1966]]:\n** '''{{flagu|Suriname}}'''\n*Last competed in [[Miss World 1979|1979]]:\n** '''{{flagu|Chile}}'''\n** '''{{flagu|El Salvador}}'''\n** '''{{flagu|Iceland}}'''\n** '''{{flagu|Tahiti}}'''\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Withdrawals===\n* '''{{flagu|Panama}}'''\n* '''{{flagu|Paraguay}}'''\n* '''{{flagu|Swaziland}}'''\n* '''{{flagu|Portugal}}''' \u2013 Paula Dos Santos who had a dual citizenship, won the Miss Portugal contest held in Johannesburg, South Africa. She flew to London, only to be told by Eric Morley that any girl from South Africa cannot participate, and that the contest has to be held in the country of the girl's origin.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs= \n<ref name=\"Weeks\">{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2245&dat=19860813&id=6uIzAAAAIBAJ&sjid=nTIHAAAAIBAJ&pg=6730,5611442&hl=en | title=Venezuelan beauties undergo rigorous training to win international pageants | newspaper=[[Lodi News-Sentinel]] | date=August 13, 1986 | accessdate=25 January 2016 | author=Weeks, Sally}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* [https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2194&dat=19810910&id=na4yAAAAIBAJ&sjid=y-4FAAAAIBAJ&pg=6495,5007549&hl=en ''Ottawa Citizen'']. September 10, 1981.\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081218082833/http://www.pageantopolis.com/international/world_1981.htm Pageantopolis \u2013 Miss World 1981]\n\n{{Miss World}}\n\n[[Category:Miss World]]\n[[Category:1981 in London]]\n[[Category:1981 beauty pageants]]\n[[Category:Beauty pageants in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Events at the Royal Albert Hall]]\n[[Category:November 1981 events in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "HKOpenTV", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePlacements", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miss_World_1981"}
