union with an Old Foe\n* Chapter 6: The Reality Here and Now\n| ChapterListCol2 =\n* Chapter 7: Cooked and Ready to Serve\n* Chapter 8: The Liberation of Lasta\n* Chapter 9: Help Arrives\n* Chapter 10: Everyone's Night Before the Final Battle\n* Chapter 11: The Dabicon is Burning\n* Chapter 12: The Victory Banquet\n* The Friedonian Military, Eastward\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 9\n | RelDate         = February 25, 2019<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/gp/product/B07NGVB562|title=\u73fe\u5b9f\u4e3b\u7fa9\u52c7\u8005\u306e\u738b\u56fd\u518d\u5efa\u8a18 9|website=[[Amazon.co.jp]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=May 29, 2019}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-80301-252-1\n | LicensedRelDate = July 20, 2019 (Digital)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://j-novel.club/v/how-a-realist-hero-rebuilt-the-kingdom-volume-9|title=''How a Realist Hero Rebuilt the Kingdom'' Vol. 9 (Digital Version)|website=[[J-Novel Club]]|accessdate=May 29, 2019}}</ref>\n | LicensedISBN    = \n | LineColor       = DB7093\n\n| ChapterList     = \n* Prologue: Tora and Tiger\n* Chapter 1: Meeting in the Sky\n* Chapter 2: The Fuuga that Halbert Saw\n* Chapter 3: A Little Adventure and a Meeting\n* Chapter 4: Finale\n* Chapter 5: Idioms Change in Meaning\n* Chapter 6: A Troublesome Present\n| ChapterListCol2 =\n* Chapter 7: The State of Various Countries\n* Epilogue 1: Family\n* Cast of Characters Arc 1: Children and Their Guardians \n* Cast of Characters Arc 2: Genia and Merula, Unveiling the Deepening Mysteries\n* Cast of Characters Arc 3: The Drill Princess of the Empire\n* Cast of Characters Arc 4: The Young Master's Awakening, the Girls' Determination\n* Cast of Characters Arc 5: The Shining Dragon \n* Epilogue 2: Welcome Home\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 10\n | RelDate         = June 25, 2019<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/gp/product/B07SQBQ5Z8?|title=\u73fe\u5b9f\u4e3b\u7fa9\u52c7\u8005\u306e\u738b\u56fd\u518d\u5efa\u8a18 10|website=[[Amazon.co.jp]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-86554-511-1\n | LicensedRelDate = October 19, 2019 (Digital)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://j-novel.club/v/how-a-realist-hero-rebuilt-the-kingdom-volume-10|title=''How a Realist Hero Rebuilt the Kingdom'' Vol. 10 (Digital Version)|website=[[J-Novel Club]]|accessdate=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n | LicensedISBN    = \n | LineColor       = DB7093\n\n| ChapterList     = \n* Prologue: The Countdown to Marriage\n* Chapter 1: The Red Oni is Blue\n* Chapter 2: Ginger Wipes it All Away\n* Chapter 3: Falling\n* Chapter 4: Heart Piercing\n* Chapter 5: The Black Tiger's Delivery\n| ChapterListCol2 =\n* Chapter 6: A Wedding Present that was Worth a Fortune\n* Chapter 7: Time to Face One Another\n* Chapter 8: Before the Ceremony\n* Final Chapter: The Wedding Ceremony\n* Bonus Story: The Happiest Queen of All\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 11\n | RelDate         = October 24, 2019<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/gp/product/B07YVBQS9Z?|title=\u73fe\u5b9f\u4e3b\u7fa9\u52c7\u8005\u306e\u738b\u56fd\u518d\u5efa\u8a18 11|website=[[Amazon.co.jp]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-86554-561-6\n | LicensedRelDate = April 26, 2020 (Digital)<ref>{{cite web |title=How a Realist Hero Rebuilt the Kingdom Volume 11 |url=https://j-novel.club/v/how-a-realist-hero-rebuilt-the-kingdom-volume-11/|website=[[J-Novel Club]]|accessdate=5 February 2020}}</ref>\n | LicensedISBN    = \n | LineColor       = DB7093\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list/footer}}\n\n=== Manga ===\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://over-lap.co.jp/bunko/genkoku/|Official website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{ann|manga|19217}}\n\n[[Category:2016 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:J-Novel Club]]\n[[Category:Light novels]]\n[[Category:Seven Seas Entertainment titles]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dnen manga]]\n[[Category:Isekai anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Upcoming anime television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = How a Realist Hero Rebuilt the Kingdom\n| image           = File:How a Realist Hero Rebuilt the Kingdom Volume 1.jpg\n| caption         = Cover of the first volume.\n| ja_kanji        = \u73fe\u5b9f\u4e3b\u7fa9\u52c7\u8005\u306e\u738b\u56fd\u518d\u5efa\u8a18\n| ja_romaji       = Genjitsushugi Y\u016bsha no \u014ckoku Saikenki\n| genre           = [[Isekai]], [[Adventure fiction|Adventure]], [[Romance novel|Romance]]|[[Harem]]\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = light novel\n| author          = Dojyomaru\n| illustrator     = Fuyuyuki\n| publisher       = Overlap\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher\n  | NA  = [[J-Novel Club]] <small>(digital)</small><br>[[Seven Seas Entertainment]] <small>(print)</small>\n}}\n| demographic     = Male\n| imprint         = Overlap Bunko\n| first           = May 25, 2016\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 11\n| volume_list     = #Light_novels\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = Dozeumaru \n| illustrator     = Satoshi Ueda\n| publisher       = Overlap\n| demographic     = ''[[Sh\u014dnen manga|Sh\u014dnen]]''\n| imprint         = \n| magazine        = Comic Gardo\n| first           = July 10, 2017\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 3\n| volume_list     = \n}} <!--\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = TV series \n| director        = \n| producer        = \n| writer          = \n| music           = \n| studio          = \n| licensee        = \n| network         = \n| first           = \n| last            = \n| episodes        = \n| episode_list    = \n}} -->\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''''How a Realist Hero Rebuilt the Kingdom'''''|\u73fe\u5b9f\u4e3b\u7fa9\u52c7\u8005\u306e\u738b\u56fd\u518d\u5efa\u8a18|Genjitsushugi Y\u016bsha no \u014ckoku Saikenki}} is a Japanese [[light novel]] series written by Dojyomaru and illustrated by Fuyuyuki, following Kazuya S\u014dma, a humanities-student-turned-hero as he pulls on his knowledge of realism and [[wikt:Machiavellianism|Machiavellianism]] in order to rebuild the kingdom. Digital publisher [[J-Novel Club]] has licensed both light novel and manga for an English release.<ref>{{cite web|title=J-Novel Club Launches Online Manga Reader, Licenses 5 Manga Titles|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-20/j-novel-club-launches-online-manga-reader-licenses-5-manga-titles/.139761}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2020, an anime television series adaptation has been announced by Overlap.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Pineda |first1=Rafael |title=How a Realist Hero Rebuilt the Kingdom Light Novels Get TV Anime |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-04-16/how-a-realist-hero-rebuilt-the-kingdom-light-novels-get-tv-anime/.158683 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=March 16, 2020 |date=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\n\"O, Hero!\"\n\nWith that clich\u00e9d line, Kazuya Souma found himself summoned to another world and his adventure\u2014\u2014did not begin. After he presents his plan to strengthen the country economically and militarily, the king cedes the throne to him and Souma finds himself saddled with ruling the nation! What's more, he's betrothed to the king's daughter now...?! In order to get the country back on its feet, Kazuya calls the wise, the talented, and the gifted to his side. Five people gather before the newly crowned Souma. Just what are the many talents and abilities they possess...?! What path will his outlook as a realist take Kazuya and the people of his country down? A revolutionary transferred-to-another-world administrative fantasy series starts here!\n\n== Characters ==\n===Main Characters===\n;{{Nihongo|'''Kazuya Souma'''|\u76f8\u99ac \u4e00\u4e5f|S\u014dma Kazuya}}\n: Summoned to another world to reportedly deal with the threat of the Demon Lord's Domain, Kazuya instead finds himself with the throne of the Kingdom of Elfrieden and the hand of Liscia Elfrieden thrown at him. Now king, Kazuya begins radical reforms in order to improve the [[standard of living]] in the kingdom. In the One Week War, Kazuya finds himself in a civil war between himself and Dukes Georg Carmine and Castor Vargas while also having to fight the Principality of Amidonia. Through a series of military strategies, Kazuya emerges victorious and annexes Amidonia (although this was entirely unplanned on his part) to create the '''Unified Kingdom of Elfrieden and Amidonia''', otherwise known as the ''Kingdom of Friedonia''. He then forges a secret alliance with Empress Maria Euphoria of the Gran Chaos Empire.\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Liscia Elfrieden'''|\u30ea\u30fc\u30b7\u30a2\u30fb\u30a8\u30eb\u30d5\u30ea\u30fc\u30c7\u30f3|R\u012bshia Erufur\u012bden}}\n: The crown princess of the Elfriedon Kingdom and Kazuya's first fianc\u00e9e, Liscia was at Kazuya's side from the very beginning. Initially dissatisfied with the unannounced engagement, Liscia soon softens and eventually develops deep feelings for Kazuya. Following the end of the One Week War, both Kazuya and Liscia affirm their love for each other, which results with the beginning of a series of nightly activities. Liscia is extremely tolerant of Kazuya's philandering, even encouraging him to take more wives, however, she remains adamant about wanting to remain the first wife.\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Aisha Udgard'''|\u30a2\u30a4\u30fc\u30b7\u30e3\u30fb\u30a6\u30c9\u30ac\u30eb\u30c9|A\u012bsha Udogarudo}}\n: Daughter of the Chief of the Dark Elves of the God Protected Forest, Aisha Udgard is one of the 5 people discovered during the gathering of the Gifted People, the first policy Kazuya implemented upon his impromptu accession to the throne. She serves as Kazuya's bodyguard and falls deeply in love with him during the [[landslide]] incident that struck her home. Following the One Week War, Aisha becomes Kazuya's second fianc\u00e9e in recognition for her actions in that war concerning the hostile Principality of Amidonia. She is an utter glutton and Kazuya himself thinks of her as a cute pet.\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Juna Doma'''|\u30b8\u30e5\u30ca\u30fb\u30c9\u30fc\u30de|Juna D\u014dma}}\n: Also known as '''Lady Canaria''' of the Elfrieden Navy's Marine force, Juna Doma is the granddaughter of Duchess Excel Walters who was sent to spy on Souma when he was first announced as the new King. She is one of the 5 people discovered during the gathering of the Gifted People. She primarily aids Kazuya in both war and in peace by being the Prima Lorelei, Kazuya's implementation of the concept of the [[Japanese idol]]. After falling in love with Kazuya, she is secretly made into his fourth fianc\u00e9e with the reason for withholding the fact of their betrothal is the possibility of starting riots when the commonfolk discovers that the famous idol is being wed.\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Roroa Amidonia'''|\u30ed\u30ed\u30a2\u30fb\u30a2\u30df\u30c9\u30cb\u30a2|Roroa Amidonia}}\n: The princess of the former Principality of Amidonia, Roroa Amidonia's craftiness had forced Kazuya to not only take her as his third fianc\u00e9e but also annex the entirety of Amidonian territory instead of just the capital in order to prevent the Turgis Republic and the Orthodox Papal State of Lunaria from getting their claws on the territory after the Principality had lost the war. She has a very keen sense of economics and heads the Silver Deer, a private company whose public face is that of her acquaintance, Sebastian Silvadia.\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Naden Delal'''|\u30ca\u30c7\u30f3\u30fb\u30c7\u30e9\u30fc\u30eb|Naden Der\u0101ru}}\n: A dragon hailing from the Star Dragon Mountain Range, Naden had been bullied for not having wings but Kazuya realized that she was a [[ryu]] and made a contract with her despite not being part of the Nothung Dragon Knight Kingdom. Naden eventually became Kazuya's fifth and final fianc\u00e9e.\n===Kingdom of Elfrieden/Kingdom of Friedonia===\n;{{nihongo|'''Hakuya Kwonmin'''|\u30cf\u30af\u30e4\u30fb\u30af\u30aa\u30f3\u30df\u30f3|Hakuya Kuonmin}}\n: The Prime Minister of the Elfrieden Kingdom (now the Kingdom of Friedonia), Hakuya Kwonmin is one of the 5 people discovered during the gathering of the Gifted People. He serves as Kazuya's right-hand man and has extremely great insight into the human psyche. He is casual friends with Jeanne Euphoria, the younger sister of Maria Euphoria, the Empress of the Gran Chaos Empire.\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Poncho Panacotta'''|\u30dd\u30f3\u30c1\u30e7\u30fb\u30d1\u30ca\u30b3\u30c3\u30bf|Poncho Panakotta}}\n: The Minister of Agriculture and Foresty of the Elfriedon Kingdom, Poncho Panacotta is one of the 5 people discovered during the gathering of the Gifted People. Due to his vast knowledge of edible delicacies, he was a key player in ending the food shortages in the kingdom. Kazuya has given him the name of '''Ishizuka'''.\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Tomoe Inui'''|\u30c8\u30e2\u30a8\u30fb\u30a4\u30cc\u30a4|Tomoe Inui}}\n: A member of the Mystic Wolf race and one of the 5 people discovered during the gathering of the Gifted People, Tomoe Inui possesses the rare ability to speak to all manner of beasts and animals. When it was revealed that she could speak to a demon, Kazuya immediately recognized her as extremely valuable and she was adopted by Albert and Elisha Elfrieden in order to shelter her, in the process, becoming Kazuya's sister-in-law-to-be and Liscia's adoptive sister.\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Halbert Magna'''|\u30cf\u30eb\u30d0\u30fc\u30c8\u30fb\u30de\u30b0\u30ca|Harub\u0101to Maguna}}\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Kaede Foxia'''|\u30ab\u30a8\u30c7\u30fb\u30d5\u30a9\u30ad\u30b7\u30a2|Kaede Fokishia}}\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Ludwin Arcs'''|\u30eb\u30c9\u30a6\u30a3\u30f3\u30fb\u30a2\u30fc\u30af\u30b9|Rudowin \u0100kusu}}\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Genia Maxwell'''|\u30b8\u30fc\u30cb\u30e3\u30fb\u30de\u30af\u30b9\u30a6\u30a7\u30eb|J\u012bnya Makusuweru}}\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Excel Walters'''|\u30a8\u30af\u30bb\u30eb\u30fb\u30f4\u30a9\u30eb\u30bf\u30fc|Ekuseru Vorut\u0101}}\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Castor Vargas'''|\u30ab\u30b9\u30c8\u30fc\u30eb\u30fb\u30d0\u30eb\u30ac\u30b9|Kasut\u014dru Barugasu}}\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Carla Vargas'''|\u30ab\u30eb\u30e9\u30fb\u30d0\u30eb\u30ac\u30b9|Karura Barugasu}}\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Georg Carmine'''|\u30b2\u30aa\u30eb\u30b0\u30fb\u30ab\u30fc\u30de\u30a4\u30f3|Georugu K\u0101main}}\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Albert Elfrieden'''|\u30a2\u30eb\u30d9\u30eb\u30c8\u30fb\u30a8\u30eb\u30d5\u30ea\u30fc\u30c7\u30f3|Aruberuto Erufur\u012bden}}\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Elisha Elfrieden'''|\u30a8\u30ea\u30b7\u30e3\u30fb\u30a8\u30eb\u30d5\u30ea\u30fc\u30c7\u30f3|Erisha Erufur\u012bden}}\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Gatsby Colbert'''|\u30ae\u30e3\u30c4\u30d3\u30fc\u30fb\u30b3\u30eb\u30d9\u30fc\u30eb|Gyatsub\u012b Korub\u0113ru}}\n\n===Principality of Amidonia===\n;{{nihongo|'''Gaius Amidonia'''|\u30ac\u30a4\u30a6\u30b9\u30fb\u30a2\u30df\u30c9\u30cb\u30a2|Gaiusu Amidonia}}\n: The last sovereign prince of the Principality of Amidonia, Gaius Amidonia the Eighth is one of the major players during the One Week War. Having trespassed the southwestern border of Elfrieden, Gaius laid siege to the city of Altomura. In a clever plan crafted by Kazuya, Hakuya, and Georg Carmine, Elfrieden was able to outwit Gaius, forcing him to flee back into Amidonia proper. In the subsequent battle, Kazuya himself ended Gaius's life but not before Gaius instructed his son to keep the flames of vengeance burning. Gaius's death resulted in the Elfrieden occupation of Amidonia's capital city, Van.\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Julis Amidonia'''|\u30e6\u30ea\u30a6\u30b9\u30fb\u30a2\u30df\u30c9\u30cb\u30a2|Yuriusu Amidonia}}\n: The son of Gaius and the older brother of Roroa, Julius Amidonia is the prince who hastily inherited his post from his father prior to his death. However, after negotiations with the Gran Chaos Empire ended and Julius was given back his country to govern, rebellions soon rose up. Julius himself was driven out of the country, fleeing to the Empire, and with Roroa's intervention, the Principality of Amidonia was annexed into Elfrieden with the added bonus of Princess Roroa's hand in marriage. \n\n===Gran Chaos Empire===\n;{{nihongo|'''Maria Euphoria'''|\u30de\u30ea\u30a2\uff1d\u30e6\u30fc\u30d5\u30a9\u30ea\u30a2|Maria Y\u016bforia}}\n: Known as the Saint, Maria Euphoria is the Empress of the Gran Chaos Empire. Having held up the Declaration of Mankind's Common Front Against the Demon Race, simply, the Mankind Declaration, she is Kazuya's idealistic opposite. After the One Week War and the annexation of Amidonia, Kazuya and Maria forged a secret alliance in order to prepare for a full-on war with the Demon Lord's Domain.\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Jeanne Euphoria'''|\u30b8\u30e3\u30f3\u30cc\uff1d\u30e6\u30fc\u30d5\u30a9\u30ea\u30a2|Jan'nu Y\u016bforia}}\n: The younger sister of Maria Euphoria, she was the one sent my the Gran Chaos Empire to take part in the negotiations of the Kingdom of Elfrieden and the Principality of Amidonia. Since then, she has been in constant contact with the Kingdom of Elfrieden (now the Kingdom of Friedonia) through the broadcasting jewel, especially with the prime minister Hakuya Kwonmin with whom she shares a close relationship with, despite having rarely met him in person.\n\n===Star Dragon Mountain Range===\n;{{nihongo|'''Tiamat'''|\u30c6\u30a3\u30a2\u30de\u30c8|Tiamato}}\n\n;{{nihongo|'''Ruby'''|\u30eb\u30d3\u30a3|Rubyi}}\n\n== Media ==\n=== Light novels ===\nOriginally starting as a web novel on [[Shousetsuka ni Narou]] but being subsequently deleted and resumed on Pixiv, ''How a Realist Hero Rebuilt the Kingdom'' as a light novel series is written by Dojyomaru and illustrated by Fuyuyuki, published by Overlap Bunko. The first volume was published in 2016. Digital English light novel publisher J-Novel Club announced their acquisition of the series on February 23, 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2017-02-17/j-novel-club-announces-full-e-book-release-calendar-for-february-and-march-2017-reddit-ama-on-feb-18th/.112350|title=J-Novel Club Announces Full E-Book Release Calendar for February and March 2017, Reddit AMA on Feb 18th|work=Anime News Network|access-date=2017-09-25|language=en}}</ref> [[Seven Seas Entertainment]] will release the light novel in print.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rule Your Own Fantasy in Seven Seas' License of HOW A REALIST HERO REBUILT THE KINGDOM Light Novel Series|url=http://www.sevenseasentertainment.com/2017/11/14/rule-your-own-fantasy-in-seven-seas-license-of-how-a-realist-hero-rebuilt-the-kingdom-light-novel-series/|website=Seven Seas Entertainment|accessdate=November 14, 2017|date=November 14, 2017}}</ref> As of October 21, 2019, ten volumes have been released in the original Japanese language.\n\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n | Language        = Japanese\n | SecondLanguage  = English\n | Width           = 75%\n | LineColor       = DB7093\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 1\n | RelDate         = May 25, 2016<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/gp/product/B01G4QUR4W|title=\u73fe\u5b9f\u4e3b\u7fa9\u52c7\u8005\u306e\u738b\u56fd\u518d\u5efa\u8a18 1|website=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 29, 2019}}</ref>\n | ISBN            =  978-4-86554-111-3\n\n | LicensedRelDate = February 23, 2017 (Digital)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://j-novel.club/v/how-a-realist-hero-rebuilt-the-kingdom-volume-1|title=''How a Realist Hero Rebuilt the Kingdom'' Vol. 1 (Digital Version)|website=[[J-Novel Club]]|accessdate=May 29, 2019}}</ref><br>September 11, 2018 (Print)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sevenseasentertainment.com/books/how-a-realist-hero-rebuilt-the-kingdom-light-novel-vol-1/|title=''How a Realist Hero Rebuilt the Kingdom'' Vol. 1 (Print Version)|website=[[Seven Seas Entertainment]] |accessdate=May 29, 2019 }}</ref>\n | LicensedISBN    = 978-1-626929-81-4\n | LineColor       = DB7093\n\n| ChapterList     = \n* Prologue \n* Chapter 1: Fundraising\n* Chapter 2: Start 